pan style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Swan Bottom and Kings Ash.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CRAG’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">primar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y concern is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> about</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the impact HS2 would have on our local communities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. However</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> our close engagement with HS2 these past </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">four</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> years has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">led us to conclu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">de</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> whatever the local interest, the current proposals are simply not in the national interest. In short there is no strategic basis on which to continue.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This submission presents our analysis of the strategic case.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Arial