2pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">A false </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">vision</span></h2><ol start="45" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It appears that whenever one of the key aspects of the strategic argument for HS2 fails to stand up to proper examination the argument is simply shifted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by the protagonists </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to another arena.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="46" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ost recently we have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> had the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Prime Minister, the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Chance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">llor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ayor of London and others </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">telling us that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HS2 is a part of a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vision for modern Britain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, that it is not possible to fully </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appraise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the benefits and that it is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">really </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘an act of faith’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In other words any argument based on strategic economic or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">social benefits h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as been abandoned in favour of ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">we know best</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Some p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rotagonists point to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">China</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as an example of a country that is forging ahead with high speed rail and suggest the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> should be doing likewise. However, this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">view of the future </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ignores</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a number of realities:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.68pt; padding-left:9.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Beijing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Shanghai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a distance of 819 miles and conventional trains were taking nearly 10 hours. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Manchester</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is only 180 miles; even </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Edinburgh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is only 400 miles.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.68pt; padding-left:9.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">All countries </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in Western economies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ave built HS railways in recent years have found them to be uneconomic. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">France</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is now cancelling new TGV projects</span><a name="_ftnref24"></a><a href="#_ftn24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Spain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’s busiest line from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Madrid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Barcelona</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> loses money</span><a name="_ftnref25"></a><a href="#_ftn25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and even </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">California</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’s high speed rail plan is in jeopardy</span><a name="_ftnref26"></a><a href="#_ftn26">[26]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.68pt; padding-left:9.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When the motorways we</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re built in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the 50s and 60s it was to serv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e the changing needs of society</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. They provided economic, long-distance transport solutions for passenger and freight</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as well as short distance hop-on, hop-off options.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.68pt; padding-left:9.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HS2 was born of 20</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> century techno</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">logy, with its inflexible movement patterns, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">constrain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> signalling systems and high energy usage. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Today in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the changing needs of society are for faster </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and more reliable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">broadband; for door-to-door</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> delivery; for flexible working and for better vide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o conferencing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><ol start="48" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">High-speed railway may be strategic in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">China</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, but it won't meet the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">'s needs for the 21</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> century.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Conclusions</span></h2><ol start="49" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As the TSC noted in 2011</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">most of the critics of HS2 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(including CRAG) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are not against investing in rail infrastructure, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> against increasing rail capacity, nor against improving region</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">al economies. B</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y taking a close interest in t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he arguments for and against HS2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e and most independent analysts simply believe that there are much better ways of achieving these aims… and much </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">better ways of spending this money.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Pu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> simply, i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f you want to spend </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">£50bn </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(or more) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">boosting the economy and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> delivering regional benefits, then there are better ways of doing it.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> If you want to spend £50bn </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">improving the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">transport </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, then</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re are better ways of doing it.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> country</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will never see a re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">turn on the ‘investment’ in HS2;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> whatever we borrow will simply increase the national debt.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">current </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">approach to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">decision-making on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HS2 is ad hoc, politically opportunistic and would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be a t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">otal anathema to decision-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">making in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a major successful corporation.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he proba</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">bility that such an investment i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n HS2 will be an extreme misuse of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> resources is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">very</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> high.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Transport Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">- Tenth Report: High Speed Rail: November 2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-24907735</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Transport Committee - Tenth Report: High Speed Rail: November 2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Amyas Morse, head of the National Audit Office, 16 May 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Transport Committee - Tenth Report: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">High Speed Rail: November 2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-17525872</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-f